This article describes the setup of FireWire (IEEE 1394, i.Link) controllers.

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
Device Drivers --->
    IEEE 1394 (FireWire) support  --->
        <*> FireWire driver stack
        <*>   OHCI-1394 controllers

''Select additional drivers,''
''e.g. for a FireWire hard drive:''

Device Drivers --->
    SCSI device support --->
        <*> SCSI device support
        <*> SCSI disk support
    IEEE 1394 (FireWire) support  --->
        <*>   Storage devices (SBP-2 protocol)
</pre>}}

=== Software ===
Portage knows the global USE flag ''ieee1394'' for enabling support for FireWire in other packages. Enabling this USE flag will pull in {{Package|sys-libs/libraw1394}} automatically:
{{File|/etc/make.conf||
USE{{=}}"... ieee1394 ..."
}}
The USE flags of libraw1394 are:
{{USEflag
|static-libs
}}

After setting this you want to update your system so the changes take effect:
{{RootCmd|emerge --ask --changed-use --deep world}}

